dct_title_s: Vilayet de l'Archipel : divisé en 4 sandjaks, 18 cazas et 19 Nahiés / par Vital Cuinet ; éditieur Ernest Leroux.
dct_description_sm: Principal meridian is Paris. Ancillary map: Vilayet de  Crète. Map shows administrative boundaries (vilayet, sandjaks, cazas); railroads in construction, three classes of roads; salt mines, and forests. Map shows administrative boundaries (vilayet, sandjaks); road, path, and forests. Vilayet de l'Archipel was a was a first level adminisrative division, vilayet  [province], of the Ottoman Empire. Covers four Sandjaks [departments]: 1. Rhodes -- 2.Chio -- 3. Mételin -- 4.Lemnos. Original map is filed in the Map/Geospatial Center, a map reproduction is attached to companion volume. Vilayet de Crète was a first level adminisrative division, vilayet  [province], of the Ottoman Empire. Covers five Sandjaks [departments]: 1. La Canée -- 2. Sphakia -- 3. Réthymo  -- 4. Candie -- 5 .Lassithi.
